1224
01:06:31,400 --> 01:06:33,039
And you are?
I'm North.

1225
01:06:33,040 --> 01:06:35,039
Always been
one of my favourite directions.

1226
01:06:35,040 --> 01:06:37,119
Mallomar?
No, thanks.

1227
01:06:37,120 --> 01:06:38,879
That bad, huh'?
What'?

1228
01:06:38,880 --> 01:06:40,719
No kid ever refuses a mallomar

1229
01:06:40,720 --> 01:06:42,919
unless he's wrestling with
some pretty heavyweight problems.

1230
01:06:42,920 --> 01:06:44,759
(Switches on TV)

1231
01:06:44,760 --> 01:06:48,159
<i>North - we miss you so much.</i>

1232
01:06:48,160 --> 01:06:50,279
<i>Please forgive us.</i>

1233
01:06:50,280 --> 01:06:53,679
<i>We made so many mistakes.</i>

1234
01:06:53,680 --> 01:06:56,839
<i>We should've appreciated you more.</i>

1235
01:06:56,840 --> 01:07:01,559
<i>If only you could give us
just one more chance.</i>

1236
01:07:01,560 --> 01:07:03,369
<i>We love you, son!</i>

1237
01:07:04,520 --> 01:07:06,249
<i>We love you very much.</i>

1238
01:07:09,400 --> 01:07:11,839
Beautiful! Works like a charm.

1239
01:07:11,840 --> 01:07:14,039
Got some pretty nice folks there, kid.

1240
01:07:14,040 --> 01:07:15,519
Huh?

1241
01:07:15,520 --> 01:07:18,039
I said you got
some pretty nice folks there.

1242
01:07:18,040 --> 01:07:19,919
Yeah. I guess so.

1243
01:07:19,920 --> 01:07:22,599
What do you mean, you guess so'?
Well, I mean...

1244
01:07:22,600 --> 01:07:25,719
And what do they mean
by give us one more chance?

1245
01:07:25,720 --> 01:07:28,479
I thought they didn't love me.
What are you, nuts?

1246
01:07:28,480 --> 01:07:32,039
That's just the thing - they didn't
always pay that much attention to me.

1247
01:07:32,040 --> 01:07:35,759
So, I left them, to find some
new folks who'd appreciate me more.

1248
01:07:35,760 --> 01:07:38,759
I searched the whole world,
but nobody was good enough.

1249
01:07:38,760 --> 01:07:41,319
Not even the Nelsons, who I just left.

1250
01:07:41,320 --> 01:07:43,759
And they weren't bad folks.

1251
01:07:43,760 --> 01:07:46,279
Maybe there's something wrong with me.

1252
01:07:46,280 --> 01:07:48,279
Ah, there's nothing wrong with you.

1253
01:07:48,280 --> 01:07:50,919
And I'm sure the Nelsons
weren't bad folks.

1254
01:07:50,920 --> 01:07:53,519
They just weren't your folks.

1255
01:07:53,520 --> 01:07:56,079
You see those people out there?
That audience?

1256
01:07:56,080 --> 01:07:59,319
They paid attention to me.
They listened to every word I said.

1257
01:07:59,320 --> 01:08:02,479
They laughed, they screamed,
they applauded. They loved me.

1258
01:08:02,480 --> 01:08:04,079
But do you think that audience

1259
01:08:04,080 --> 01:08:07,559
is gonna make me a cup of tea
if I'm not feeling well?

1260
01:08:07,560 --> 01:08:11,610
Are they gonna help me when I get
in a fight with my best friend?

1261
01:08:12,560 --> 01:08:15,679
Or - God forbid - I get in girl trouble.
Who am I going to turn to?

1262
01:08:15,680 --> 01:08:18,759
I'll give you a hint -
it's not that audience.

1263
01:08:18,760 --> 01:08:21,439
Oh, my God. What have I done?
I'll tell you.

1264
01:08:21,440 --> 01:08:25,119
You've realised something that takes
most people a lifetime to figure out.

1265
01:08:25,120 --> 01:08:27,479
Some people
never figure it out at all -

1266
01:08:27,480 --> 01:08:29,959
that a bird in the hand is always greener

1267
01:08:29,960 --> 01:08:32,201
than the grass
under the other guy's bushes.

1268
01:08:36,320 --> 01:08:37,799
L...it's a metaphor

1269
01:08:37,800 --> 01:08:40,280
used mostly by gardeners
and landscape people in general.

1270
01:08:43,960 --> 01:08:46,199
Hey, kid...

1271
01:08:46,200 --> 01:08:47,839
Hey, kid. Where are you going'?

1272
01:08:47,840 --> 01:08:49,519
Home. I miss my parents.

1273
01:08:49,520 --> 01:08:51,959
How are you going to get to the airport'?

1274
01:08:51,960 --> 01:08:53,919
You got a car?
No - I'm 11.

1275
01:08:53,920 --> 01:08:55,763
Alright, then - we'd better take mine.

1276
01:09:02,080 --> 01:09:05,084
(PLANE RUMBLES OVERHEAD)

1277
01:09:07,800 --> 01:09:12,119
Thanks for everything, Mr Fingers.
Make it Joey. And you're welcome.

1278
01:09:12,120 --> 01:09:15,719
And remember, kid - if you can't
stand the heat, stay out of Miami.

1279
01:09:15,720 --> 01:09:18,439
What does that metaphor mean?
What metaphor?

1280
01:09:18,440 --> 01:09:20,399
You ever been down there in August?

1281
01:09:20,400 --> 01:09:23,119
Your balls stick to your leg
like crazy glue. Goodbye.

1282
01:09:23,120 --> 01:09:25,359
<i>And so,
North finally found the parents</i>

1283
01:09:25,360 --> 01:09:27,039
<i>he'd always been looking for.</i>

1284
01:09:27,040 --> 01:09:29,359
<i>Much to his surprise,
they were his own.</i>

1285
01:09:29,360 --> 01:09:32,599
<i>With a song in his heart
and a smile on his face,</i>

1286
01:09:32,600 --> 01:09:34,479
<i>North prepared
to board the final plane</i>

1287
01:09:34,480 --> 01:09:36,959
<i>bound for the loving arms
of those very parents.</i>

1288
01:09:36,960 --> 01:09:39,439
Where do you think you're going?
I'm going home!

1289
01:09:39,440 --> 01:09:42,039
Not on this plane, you're not.
Why not?

1290
01:09:42,040 --> 01:09:44,771
It says here you're dead.

1291
01:09:47,000 --> 01:09:48,519
But... I'm not!

1292
01:09:48,520 --> 01:09:51,839
How can I be sure?
I'm standing here talking to you.

1293
01:09:51,840 --> 01:09:53,679
I know, and that scares me.

1294
01:09:53,680 --> 01:09:55,045
Since I don't scare easily,

1295
01:09:55,080 --> 01:09:57,719
you can imagine how it will affect
the other passengers.

1296
01:09:57,720 --> 01:10:00,399
But I'm not dead!
Sorry, I can't take that chance.

1297
01:10:00,400 --> 01:10:03,199
Hey, it's North - he's alive!
What's he doing here?

1298
01:10:03,200 --> 01:10:04,879
This plane's headed to his hometown.

1299
01:10:04,880 --> 01:10:06,879
He's trying to return to his parents.

1300
01:10:06,880 --> 01:10:09,079
It'll ruin everything. Let's get him!

1301
01:10:09,080 --> 01:10:12,084
